OL,4,Cstruggling to cast their ballot
OL,5,Cprivately
OL,7,FThe standard aid currently in use is
OL,8,Fthe tactile voting device, a thin
OL,9,Fplastic template which can be placed
OL,10,Fover a ballot paper to help locate
OL,11,Fwhere to vote for your preferred
OL,12,Fcandidate.
OL,14,FHowever, as it doesn't provide the
OL,15,Fnames of the candidates, many blind or
OL,16,Fpartially sighted people need further
OL,17,Fassistance to vote.
OL,19,FVoters can request a McGonagle Reader,
OL,20,Fa tactile device with an integrated
OL,21,Faudio player.
